# App Hub Publisher ‚Äî Project Rules

This repo is a **publisher kit** for **App Hub** (desktop host + app store). It does not ship sample apps. Publishers (or AI agents) create apps under `apps/<slug>/`. See `AGENTS.md` and `README.md` at repo root.

## Publisher URLs ‚Äî local config only (required reading)

**All Hub URLs live in `apphub.publisher.json` at repo root.** That file is **gitignored** ‚Äî each publisher copies from `apphub.publisher.example.json` and fills in their own values. **Never put real URLs in tracked files** (README, rules, or commits).

| Key | Purpose |
|-----|---------|
| `integration_docs_url` | Machine-readable integration contract (JSON) from your App Hub operator |
| `hub_portal_url` | Your App Hub portal (install, launch, store, upload) |
| `upstream.auto_file_issues` | When `true`, agents may run `upstream-report` on platform gaps; default `false` for public clones |
| `upstream.packages_repo` | Allowlisted repo for issue templates (e.g. `kennofizet/apphub-packages`) |
| `upstream.kit_repo` | Allowlisted repo for kit PR + issue templates |
| `upstream.github_token_file` | Path to gitignored PAT (default `.github-token.local`) |

Setup after clone:

```bash
cp apphub.publisher.example.json apphub.publisher.json
# Edit apphub.publisher.json with your URLs (do not commit this file)
```

**App Hub** may inject URLs into this file when the publisher connects their instance.

### Agent behavior

1. **Read `apphub.publisher.json` first** (create from `apphub.publisher.example.json` if missing).
2. If `integration_docs_url` is **empty or missing**, **stop and ask the user** for their integration docs URL. Do not invent API hosts or paths.
3. If `hub_portal_url` is **empty or missing**, ask the user for their App Hub portal URL when deploy, testing, or store steps are needed.
4. When set, fetch `integration_docs_url` and treat it as the authoritative contract (`schema_version`, routes, bridge). HTTP paths in this rule file are **examples** ‚Äî use `http.base_path` from the fetched docs.
5. **Upstream report:** When you hit a **platform/contract gap** (not fixable in app code) ‚Äî only if `upstream.auto_file_issues` is `true` in local config **or** the user explicitly requests it. Add `docs/upstream-issues/<tag>/meta.json` + `body.md` (`meta.repo` must be `upstream.packages_repo` or `upstream.kit_repo`). Run `npm run upstream-report -- issue <tag>` (or `kit-pr` / `all`). Use `--yes` for a one-shot when auto-file is off. **Do not** ask the user to open GitHub manually when auto-file is enabled. Auth: `GITHUB_TOKEN` env ‚Üí `.github-token.local` ‚Üí git credential. Issue tag folders are gitignored; kit PR template in `docs/upstream-kit-pr/`.

**Official contract:** value of `integration_docs_url` in `apphub.publisher.json` only (not hardcoded in this repo).

## Language ‚Äî English only (authoring)

All **source code**, **documentation**, **comments**, **commit messages**, **Cursor rules**, and **README files** in this repo must be written in **English**.

- Identifiers, function names, types, API payloads, logs, and error messages in code: **English**
- Inline comments and JSDoc/TSDoc: **English**
- User-facing UI copy: still localized via i18n (`en` + `vi` locale files) ‚Äî see below

Do not add Vietnamese (or other language) prose in code, docs, or rules. Vietnamese strings belong only in `locales/vi.json` (and English in `locales/en.json`).

## Monorepo layout

- One app = **one folder** at repo root: `apps/<slug>/`
- Each app **builds, deploys, and runs independently** (own `package.json`, `manifest.json`, optional backend)
- No cross-imports between apps; share via `packages/` only when necessary (e.g. `packages/apphub-bridge/`)

```
apps/<slug>/
  PLAN.md          # living plan + per-step checklists (required)
  tests/           # optional ‚Äî your unit/integration tests (commit if you track the app)
    sandbox-apphub/  # App Hub pre-deploy harness (gitignored ‚Äî copy template)
      manifest.json
      cases/         # one .mjs per user action / save path
      fixtures/      # e.g. sample.mp4 ‚Äî not committed
  src/
    components/
    modules/       # api, stores, composables
    locales/       # en.json, vi.json
    themes/
  manifest.json    # runtime_type, permissions, api_urls
  package.json
  README.md
```

## Root `.gitignore` ‚Äî applies to all apps

Maintain **one** `.gitignore` at the **repo root**. Do not duplicate per app unless an app has an exceptional local-only artifact ‚Äî then add a one-line pointer in the app README, not a second full ignore file.

**Must be ignored (root patterns):**

| Category | Patterns |
|----------|----------|
| Dependencies | `node_modules/`, `.pnp`, `.pnp.js` |
| Build output | `dist/`, `build/`, `out/`, `.output/`, `.nuxt/`, `.next/`, `.vite/`, `*.tsbuildinfo` |
| Deploy bundles | `*.zip` (hosted Hub zips; exception only for intentional docs assets) |
| Secrets | `.env`, `.env.*` (allow `!.env.example`), `*.pem`, `*.key`, `secrets/`, launch-token files |
| Logs | `logs/`, `*.log`, `*-debug.log*` |
| Test/coverage | `coverage/`, `.nyc_output/`, `playwright-report/`, `test-results/` |
| Sandbox app tests | `apps/*/tests/sandbox-apphub/` (harness cases + fixtures; template in `tools/test-harness/templates/app-tests/`) |
| Sandbox Hub config | `apphub.test.json`, `.apphub-token.dev.local`, `.apphub-token.user.local`, `logs/test-harness/`, `tools/test-harness/stack/hub-frontend/`, `tools/test-harness/stack/hub-backend/` |
| Caches | `.cache/`, `.turbo/`, `.parcel-cache/`, `.eslintcache`, `.stylelintcache` |
| OS/editor junk | `.DS_Store`, `Thumbs.db`, `.idea/`, swap files ‚Äî **do not** ignore `.cursor/rules/` |
| Hosting metadata | `.vercel/`, `.netlify/` |

Never commit: `.env`, tokens, `launch_token`, private keys, or generated `dist/` / deploy zips.

When adding a new tool stack (e.g. Python, Rust), extend **root** `.gitignore` once so every app inherits it.

## Per-app plan and checklists ‚Äî required

Before starting work on an app (new or existing), create or open `apps/<slug>/PLAN.md`.

### PLAN.md structure

```markdown
# <App name> ‚Äî Plan

## Goal
One paragraph: what this app does and success criteria.

## Phases

### Phase 1 ‚Äî <name>
**Status:** not started | in progress | done

- [ ] Step 1.1 ‚Äî ...
- [ ] Step 1.2 ‚Äî ...

### Phase 2 ‚Äî <name>
...
```

### Rules for plans and checklists

1. **Plan before doing** ‚Äî outline phases and steps in `PLAN.md` before implementation (scaffold, feature, fix, or publish).
2. **Checklist per step** ‚Äî every phase has concrete `- [ ]` items; one item = one verifiable outcome.
3. **Update on every change** ‚Äî when you start, edit, finish, or drop work:
   - Mark items `[x]` when done
   - Add new steps if scope grows
   - Set phase **Status** (`not started` ‚Üí `in progress` ‚Üí `done`)
   - Add a short **Changelog** section at the bottom with date + what changed (optional but recommended)
4. **Keep in sync** ‚Äî if code or manifest changes without updating `PLAN.md`, update the plan in the same session before considering the task complete.
5. **English only** ‚Äî same language rule as code and docs.

Agents and contributors must read `PLAN.md` at the start of work on an app and update it before finishing.

## Runtime type ‚Äî pick the right one

| | `hosted` | `iframe` |
|---|----------|----------|
| Host | Zip on Hub ‚Üí `‚Ä¶/apps/{slug}/runtime/` | Publisher hosts SPA at `entry_url` (HTTPS) |
| Storage | `localStorage` shim ‚Äî **await `window.__APPHUB_STORAGE__?.ready`** before first read | Normal `localStorage`/`sessionStorage` on publisher origin |
| Use when | Small tools, demos, no publisher HTTPS host | Full SPAs, auth, domain you control |

**Required manifest fields:** `runtime_type`, `permissions[]`, `api_urls[]` (if backend exists).  
For iframe, also: `entry_url`, optional `healthcheck_url`.

## Hosted runtime ‚Äî zip layout and troubleshooting

Follow `audiences.publisher.hosted_runtime_troubleshooting` in the integration docs (schema `1.11.1+`). Summary for agents:

### Zip contract (hosted register)

- `manifest.json` **inside** the zip (at root or shallowest folder).
- Entry file: `manifest.main` / `index.html` must exist in the zip.
- Zip **build output only** (e.g. `dist/` contents) ‚Äî never `node_modules`, `.cmd`, `.ps1`, or dev tooling.
- Typical layout at zip root: `manifest.json`, `index.html`, `assets/*.js`, `assets/*.css`.
- Max bundle size per integration docs (commonly ~50 MB).

### JavaScript / ES modules

- **ES modules are supported** (`<script type="module">`). Hashed names like `index-BmAhrHFo.js` come from **your bundler** (Vite), not a Hub-injected loader.
- Hub **does not** remove `type="module"`. It rewrites `src`/`href` to append `launch_token`, injects the storage shim, and serves `.js` as `application/javascript`.
- **`Cannot use import statement outside a module`** usually means a chunk returned **401, 404, or HTML** (browser runs error body as classic script), or `index.html` lost `type="module"`. Check DevTools Network: all `.js` ‚Üí 200. **Not** a CSP `frame-ancestors` issue.

### CSP `frame-ancestors 'self'`

- Nested chain: product shell ‚Üí Hub iframe ‚Üí hosted runtime on API origin.
- **Publishers cannot fix this in the zip.** Platform team must allow Hub and product origins (`APPHUB_ALLOWED_HUB_ORIGINS`, `APPHUB_ALLOWED_PRODUCT_ORIGINS`). Report framing errors with your Hub and product URLs.

### Build tools (hosted)

- **Vite 5/6** with `type="module"` and `base: './'` is the recommended path. Zip `dist/` + `manifest.json` at zip root.
- IIFE builds are optional for debugging wiring only ‚Äî not required for production.

## Bridge ‚Äî required integration

### Connection flow

1. User opens app ‚Üí Hub calls `POST /apps/{slug}/launch` ‚Üí `entry_url` + `launch_token` + `scopes_granted`
2. App loads in a Hub window
3. Listen for **`apphub:bridge:ready`** (or use `window.AppHubBridge`)
4. UI uses `display_user`; **server auth** uses `GET bridge/user` from publisher backend

### postMessage protocol (channel: `apphub:bridge`)

| Direction | Event | Purpose |
|-----------|-------|---------|
| Parent ‚Üí child | `apphub:bridge:ready` | Sends `context` (app_slug, launch_token, scopes_granted, display_user, ‚Ä¶) |
| Child ‚Üí parent | `apphub:bridge:call` | `{ id, method, args }` |
| Parent ‚Üí child | `apphub:bridge:result` | `{ id, ok, result?, error? }` |

**Bridge methods:** `requestPermission`, `sendDesktopMessage`, `setTaskbarBadge`, `saveFile`, `reportError`  
Copy/load `docs/sdk-stub.js` into your bundle or use `window.AppHubBridge`.

Read `audiences.publisher.bridge.javascript_api` in the fetched integration docs for signatures ‚Äî do not guess bridge methods.

### Permissions

| Scope | Notes |
|-------|-------|
| `user.read` | User id + display name ‚Äî granted at install |
| `user.profile` | Avatar, locale, etc. ‚Äî granted at install |
| `desktop.notify` | For `POST bridge/notify` from **publisher backend** only |
| `desktop.message` | Request via `requestPermission` during session |
| `desktop.badge` | Request via `requestPermission` during session |
| `desktop.download` | **Hosted export** ‚Äî declare in `manifest.permissions[]`; request at runtime; use `bridge.saveFile` (see below) |

### Hosted file export / download (required reading for save features)

**Do not** use `<a download>` or `URL.createObjectURL` alone in **hosted** runtimes ‚Äî the opaque sandbox blocks normal browser downloads.

**Correct pattern** (from integration docs `bridge.javascript_api.saveFile`):

1. Add **`desktop.download`** to `manifest.json` `permissions[]`.
2. Implement **`saveFile`** on your bridge stub (see `docs/sdk-stub.js`).
3. On export: `await bridge.requestPermission('desktop.download')` then `await bridge.saveFile({ filename, mime, data })` where `data` is **base64 string** or **ArrayBuffer**.
4. Use a **short timeout** (e.g. 5s) on bridge calls ‚Äî missing Hub handlers otherwise hang ~30s.
5. Fallback UI: copy image to clipboard, open blob in new tab, right-click preview ‚Äî never only a hidden programmatic click.

**Re-install** may be required after adding `desktop.download` to an already-installed app.

### Hosted i18n ‚Äî bundle locales, do not fetch

`fetch('./locales/en.json')` from hosted JS often returns **401** (no `launch_token` on fetch; cookie not sent in opaque sandbox). **Import/bundle** `en.json` and `vi.json` into your JS bundle (Vite `import en from './locales/en.json'`).

### Hosted UI ‚Äî modals inside `.ps-app`

CSS theme variables (`--ps-*`) are defined on `.ps-app`. Mount dialogs/toasts **inside** `#ps-app`, not `document.body`, or modals render unstyled.

### Kit testing before publish

From repo root (requires `apphub.publisher.json` + `.apphub-token.local`):

```bash
npm run apphub -- test <slug>      # launch + asset checks + contract hints
npm run apphub -- register <slug>   # upload latest release zip
npm run apphub -- launch <slug>     # smoke-test launch URL
```

### Two user data tiers ‚Äî do not mix them up

- **display_only** (`getDisplayUser()`, `display_user` on ready): greetings, UI labels ‚Äî **not for auth**
- **authoritative** (`GET bridge/user` or `POST verify-launch-token` on publisher server): authorization, audit, server-side API

### launch_token ‚Äî security

- Short-lived secret; treat like a password
- **Never** log, show in UI, or send to third parties
- Publisher backend passes token to `GET bridge/user` (headers `X-AppHub-Launch-Token`, `X-AppHub-App-Slug`)

### HTTP companion (publisher backend on `api_urls`)

- `GET bridge/user` ‚Äî scoped user snapshot (requires `user.read` on token)
- `POST bridge/notify` ‚Äî desktop notifications (requires `desktop.notify`)
- `POST verify-launch-token` ‚Äî one-time token verification; caller IP must match `api_urls`
- App frontend calls **publisher backend proxy** ‚Äî do not call Hub bridge HTTP directly from iframe

## Deploy

- **hosted:** `dist/` ‚Üí zip + `manifest.json` ‚Üí `POST /apps/register` (draft) ‚Üí approval ‚Üí store
- **iframe:** manifest with `runtime_type: iframe` + `entry_url` ‚Üí register JSON or drop manifest on Hub desktop
- **local:** manifest on Hub desktop ‚Äî private install, not listed in store

Portal URL for upload and testing: **`hub_portal_url`** in `apphub.publisher.json` (local file, not committed).

## Pre-deploy sandbox testing (required)

**Never register or deploy to production Hub until the full local sandbox gate passes.**

Use `apphub.test.json` + `npm run test:harness` (not `apphub.publisher.json`). Stack must use real packages when possible (`stack.backend: "real"`).

### Gate command (run before every register/deploy)

```bash
npm run test:harness -- stack up          # if not already running
npm run test:harness -- run pre-deploy --slug <slug>
```

`pre-deploy` runs: API health ‚Üí register/launch ‚Üí dual-account ‚Üí **all** `apps/<slug>/tests/sandbox-apphub/cases/*.mjs`.

### Per-feature test files (required per app)

Each meaningful user action gets **one case file** under `apps/<slug>/tests/sandbox-apphub/cases/`:

| Example file | What it verifies |
|--------------|------------------|
| `01-launch.mjs` | `POST /launch`, runtime `index.html` 200 |
| `03-upload.mjs` | File picker + upload path (Playwright) |
| `04-comment.mjs` | Add/save comment (Playwright) |
| `05-export.mjs` | Export / `bridge.saveFile` (Playwright) |

Register cases in `apps/<slug>/tests/sandbox-apphub/manifest.json`. **Copy** template from `tools/test-harness/templates/app-tests/` ‚Äî only `sandbox-apphub/` is **gitignored**; you may add your own tests alongside under `apps/<slug>/tests/` (unit tests, mocks, etc.).

```bash
npm run test:harness -- list app <slug>
npm run test:harness -- run app <slug>              # all cases
npm run test:harness -- run app <slug> --case upload  # one case after a code change
```

- **API cases** (`type: "api"`) ‚Äî always run; no browser.
- **Playwright cases** (`type: "playwright"`) ‚Äî set `playwright.enabled: true` in `apphub.test.json`; skip gracefully when off.

When adding a feature, add or update a case file **in the same session** before marking `PLAN.md` done.

Agents: **block** `npm run apphub -- register` / production deploy steps until `pre-deploy` passes for that slug.

## i18n (en / vi) ‚Äî required for UI

- All user-visible strings via i18n; always ship `locales/en.json` and `locales/vi.json`
- Sync locale with Hub when `user.profile` or bridge context provides it
- No hardcoded UI text in components (use locale keys)

## Dark / Light mode ‚Äî required

- Support both themes; use semantic CSS variables / design tokens
- App must be usable in both modes inside Hub windows
- Persist preference locally when running standalone

## Code quality

- Clean, maintainable code; clear module separation (UI / logic / API)
- Prefer TypeScript; type bridge context, manifest, and API payloads
- Handle denied permissions gracefully in UI
- Never commit `.env`, `launch_token`, or secrets

## Pre-publish checklist

- [ ] `PLAN.md` updated ‚Äî all completed steps marked, phases reflect current state
- [ ] `apps/<slug>/tests/sandbox-apphub/manifest.json` + case files for each major user action (local/gitignored ‚Äî copy template)
- [ ] **Sandbox gate passed:** `npm run test:harness -- run pre-deploy --slug <slug>` (local stack, JSONL logs)
- [ ] `manifest.json` has correct `runtime_type`, `permissions`, `api_urls`
- [ ] Listens for `apphub:bridge:ready`; hosted: awaits `__APPHUB_STORAGE__.ready`
- [ ] Server auth via publisher backend; never trust `display_user` for authorization
- [ ] `launch_token` not exposed in client logs or UI
- [ ] Full `en` + `vi` locale files; dark + light themes usable
- [ ] Launch flow tested: `npm run apphub -- test <slug>` (or `launch <slug>`) ‚Üí assets 200, locales bundled
- [ ] Hosted export uses `desktop.download` + `bridge.saveFile` (not `<a download>` only)
- [ ] Dialogs/overlays mounted inside `.ps-app` (theme CSS variables)
- [ ] `apphub.publisher.json` filled locally (file is gitignored ‚Äî never commit real URLs)
